&lt;div class="section" id="github-deployment-and-version-control"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a class="toc-backref" href="https://jiaweizhuang.github.io/blog/personal-website-with-jupyter-support-using-nikola-and-github-page/#id4"&gt;4   Github deployment and version control&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most posts mention deployment at the last but I feel it necessary to mention it at the very beginning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A well version-controlled &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;src&lt;/tt&gt; branch, with only core files and meaningful commit messages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A automatically generated &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;master&lt;/tt&gt; branch for deployment. With messy html files but you never need to care. With only &lt;cite&gt;auto commit&lt;/cite&gt; messages and comprehensible commit history.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="change-theme"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a class="toc-backref" href="https://jiaweizhuang.github.io/blog/personal-website-with-jupyter-support-using-nikola-and-github-page/#id5"&gt;5   Change theme&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use Twitter's well-known boostrap4. Can tweak theme with bootwathc but I find the default theme perfect for me.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="set-non-blog-layout"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a class="toc-backref" href="https://jiaweizhuang.github.io/blog/personal-website-with-jupyter-support-using-nikola-and-github-page/#id6"&gt;6   Set non-blog layout&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Well-documented in official tutorial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emphasize the difference between &lt;cite&gt;post&lt;/cite&gt; and &lt;cite&gt;page&lt;/cite&gt;: Unlike &lt;cite&gt;new_post&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;nikola new_page&lt;/cite&gt; will not be indexed unless you add it]
Move to blog posts to &lt;cite&gt;blog&lt;/cite&gt; folder&lt;/p&gt;
